The link for the chosen Dataset is: Marathon_finishers Here I am going to read the data Set with read.csv options(warn=-1) df <- read.csv("C://Users//3165182957//OneDrive - Florida Polytechnic University//Desktop//Data Visualization//Mini project_2//data//marathon_results_2017.csv", header = TRUE) Cleaning the data set During data cleansing, all the existing data in a database is reviewed and deleted or updated if it is outdated, incomplete, incorrect, improperly formatted, duplicate, or irrelevant. Data cleansing usually involves cleaning up data compiled in one area. You can define pace simply as your speed while running, and it is often defined as the average time it takes you to run one mile during a longer run. library(chron) library(ggplot2) library(dplyr) library(lubridate) ## ## Attaching package: 'lubridate' ## The following objects are masked from 'package:chron': ## ## days, hours, minutes, seconds, years ## The following objects are masked from 'package:base': ## ## date, intersect, setdiff, union options(warn=-1) # ,'BRA','GBR','CAN','BRA','CHN','GER' selected_countries = c('USA') selected_states = c('AK',"FL","CA","WA","CO","CT") df_selected_countries = df[(df$Country %in% (selected_countries)),] df_selected_countries = df[(df$State %in% (selected_states)),] df_selected_countries <- na.omit(df_selected_countries) df_selected_countries_stats =df_selected_countries[,c("Country",'State','age_group',"X5K","Pace","X10K")] df_selected_countries_stats_t1 = df_selected_countries_stats %>% group_by(Country,State,age_group) %>% summarise(avg_pace = mean(times(Pace)), avg_5k = mean(times(X5K)), avg_10k = mean(times(X10K)), ) ## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Country', 'State'. You can override using ## the `.groups` argument. df_selected_countries_stats_t1$avg_pace_10k_secs <- apply(df_selected_countries_stats_t1, 1, FUN = function(x) period_to_seconds(hms(x[6])) ) df_selected_countries_stats$avg_pace_10k_secs <- apply(df_selected_countries_stats, 1, FUN = function(x) period_to_seconds(hms(x[6])) ) df_selected_countries_stats_t1 %>% ggplot(aes(x = State, y = avg_pace_10k_secs)) + geom_point(aes(colour = age_group)) + facet_wrap( ~ age_group) #geom_smooth(method='lm') The average paces of athletes in six different states are compared. These are (Arkansas, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Florida, Washington); in every age group, Arkansas is lower than other states, whereas the average pace of 41-83 is fairly similar, but there are huge differences in the other age groups.
